---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import ProfilePic from '../assets/homepage-cover.jpeg'
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	pubDate={new Date('March 03 2026')}
	heroImage={ProfilePic}
>
	<p>
		Hi, I’m Yago. I write here to think in public, share small lessons from building, and keep
		track of the ideas I want to revisit. I’m drawn to clear language, solid craft, and work
		that’s useful long after the first read.
	</p>
	<p>
		My days are a mix of shipping, debugging, and refining. I like systems that are simple on
		the surface and sturdy underneath, and I care about the details that make a project feel
		inevitable rather than accidental. When I learn something worth keeping, this is where it
		goes.
	</p>
	<p>
		This blog is a workbench more than a stage. You’ll find notes on tools, workflows, and the
		mindset I try to bring to my work, along with occasional detours into design, writing, or
		whatever is pulling at my curiosity.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you’ve found your way here, I hope you leave with something useful or at least a clear
		idea you can carry into your own projects. Thanks for reading and for keeping me honest.
	</p>
</Layout>
